result.name: NOC Mercury

reviews.text: Just stopped into NOC’s new location and it’s so bright and clean and beautiful. The food is scrumptious and fresh, and the coffee well made. Everything came out quickly and the staff were friendly as well. I’ll definitely be back for this!
This a nice place and coffee is nice. And saw a singer in there too. 😍 Toilet is big and clean with Dyson hands driers  😂

Nice new coffee shop near my office, convenient! Price of coffee is more expensive than the other coffee shops in the area but you can be assured that the quality at NOC is perfect. I like that you can choose between two coffee roasts - sweet fruity blend VS dark nutty blend. The menu is quite simple: black (no milk) VS white (with milk). Though you can specifically request cappuccino, latte, flat white, to your liking. Difference between black VS white is HKD5. If dining in, they serve the coffee in white cups as opposed to paper cups. I like! 

Knocking off a star because the air conditioning was freezing! It was blowing right at my back when I sat down and gave me a stomach ache within 5 minutes.

They have 1 bathroom inside.

Love the clean, minimalistic design of this place. Gives it a Scandinavian vibe and its opening has definitely upped the cool factor of the Tin Hau neighbourhood. Coffee is great and there is a selection of cafe food eg eggs benedict, avocado toast and cakes. That said, the food, whilst good, can be improved on
Good coffee and their avocado smash is delicious. Spacious and comfy.
